description:
As a Full-Stack .NET Developer, you will develop digital products and service-based platforms. You will collaborate with other team members across the DACH region, Poland and Scandinavia to deliver high-quality web solutions to our international clients.




As a software developer at Forte Digital:




 * You will design, build and implement web applications and technology platforms for our customers across Europe
 * You will work in an environment where software quality matters and where continues delivery, performance, or security are part of our DNA
 * You will work with people full of curiosity and a passion for software development
 * You will be part of the organisation without hierarchy and endless processes




An ideal candidate is a person who has a good understanding of the web platform and experience in creating web applications; knows the software development lifecycle; is open to new technologies and tools; wants to develop and values high-quality code.




Requirements




 * Strong, innovative and initiative-seeking approach to problem solving and finding solutions;
 * Proficiency in Object-Oriented Programming & Design;
 * Good knowledge C# and .NET Core (or .NET Framework);
 * Good understanding of web platform and building web API;
 * Working knowledge of JavaScript/TypeScript;
 * Willingness to test your code;
 * Good understanding of web platform and building web API;
 * Familiarity with team collaboration tools (e.g. Azure DevOps, Gitlab, JIRA);
 * Strong communication and collaboration skills;
 * Good verbal and written communication skills in English are a must;
 * Willingness to travel to work closely with your clients




Nice to have:




 * Experience with modern JavaScript UI frameworks (React or Angular or Vue);
 * Experience working with Continuous Integration / Continuous Delivery;
 * Experience working with cloud services (e.g. Azure, AWS);
 * Experience working with distributed, multidisciplinary teams




Benefits




At Forte Digital, our interdisciplinary teams create digital digital products and services in close collaboration with our clients. We create long-term solutions built on digital service platforms across the DACH region, Scandinavia and Poland.




 * We work with cutting-edge technology which has always been part of our DNA and we want our employees to define what technologies our clients use next;
 * Work in a startup environment full of growth-oriented people who want to have an impact on the services we deliver;
 * A team of experienced developers helping each other improve their skills;
 * Competitive salary and benefits package, including health care, sport membership, and more;
 * We focus on skills development and learning opportunities for your professional growth (a whole day set aside for professional development every month);
 * We focus on stable and ambitious customers with a long horizon;
 * We offer you a vibrant workplace culture with many different community events throughout the year;
 * Flexible working hours and the possibility to work from our offices in Oslo, Krak√≥w and to work fully remotely;
 * Possibility to spend time in our castle property in France
